<h3 class="date"><a href="/2005/dec/05/">&#x27a0;</a> December 5, 2005</h3>


<div class="row">
    <div class="span12">


    
    <div class="well" id="why_the_current_allyoucaneat_m" >

        
        <a name="002147"></a>
        

        <h4><a class="taggedlink linklink" href="http://www.rhapsody.com/album?albumId=96928">Why the current all-you-can-eat music service providers suck: An illustration</a></h4>

        

        <p>As a Rhapsody subscriber, I&#8217;m able to listen to only nine out of fourteen tracks from the Beck album &#8216;Midnite Vultures&#8217; without forking out another $10.  What idiot in charge of licensing decided that &#8216;Mixed Bizness&#8221; was fine for free download, but that the excellent &#8220;Debra&#8221; is blocked?  Record companies:  You&#8217;re morons, and this is why no-one uses your crappy &#8220;legal&#8221; alternatives to file-sharing.</p>

        <div class="row-fluid">
            <div class="span10">
                
